<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-738-169  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 738 169.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Network World  Dec 24 1990 v7 n52 p9(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Financial services provider hands MCI $15m data deal. (BridgeInformation Systems Inc signs $15 million contract to buildprivate data network)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Brown, Jim.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Bridge Information Systems Inc has signed a $15 million, five-yearcontract with MCI Communications Corp to build a nationwideprivate network based on 10 points of presence that willco-allocate the financial service firm's modems and multiplexersto save money.andP;  The network will link Bridge's clients with itsdata centers in St. Louis and will save overhead costs because theuser will not have to rent office space and hire personnel inmultiple locations.andP;  It will replace existing analog circuits andreduce the number of circuits needed for multiple access.andP;  Bridgepreviously relied on several different carriers for its alternaterouting needs; the new network will route data between customersites and data centers over two 56K-bps backbones for improveddisaster recovery.andP;  Customers will no longer need separate linksfor each Bridge service they receive.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   MCI Communications Corp. (Contracts)Bridge Information Systems Inc. (Contracts).andO;Ticker:    MCIC.andO;Topic:     Private NetworksContractsLong-Distance Telephone ServicesData CommunicationsFinancial Services.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>